Vice President Mike Pence wrote an op-ed for USA Today, highlighting the accomplishments of the Trump administration in its first year. Pence praises the president's leadership in reviving the American economy, with nearly 1.5 million new jobs created and a booming stock market. He also mentions the approval of the Keystone and Dakota pipelines and the end of the "war on coal." Pence emphasizes the appointment of originalist judges to uphold the Constitution and the confirmation of Justice Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court. He concludes by stating that this has been a year of accomplishments and that they are just getting started.